         DigitalBlasphemy is a ver good site.  Haven't been on it much.  Heh, both my laptop and my tower at home are rendering 2 pictures in Bryce to Poster size for my spot on zazzle.  Only trouble about making large 3D pics, or even small ones but you use alot of Volumes (like gasses and such) instead of solid objects (like a wall, or a hammer), the rendering time can take a loooong time.  I have a fairly kick arse system (AMD 1700+, 768Mb o' RAM), and a couple o' my pics that I have to re-render to poster size will take at least a day of solid running.</P><P><font size=1>Racaus Camarillo<BR>Quellious<BR>Healers United (isn't that a hoot?)</font id=size1><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
