        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         GLad you enjoyed the pic! :)</P><P>Clothes are a PITA to make :/ You can get tons off the Net from Renderosity etc, true posebale clothes count as "people" and go in the People folder in Poser, and you add them to your original figure (double tick symbol) then CONFORM TO...and set them to conform to your original person (Figure 1 usually) then they inherit all his bends and such.<BR>(I like Inside the Chrome Ship by way!)<BR>Often you can paint hair and clothing in afterwards in 2d, </P><P><a href="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/ogre1.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/ogre1.jpg</a></P><P>The hair, smoke, green cap. most of the flames and kilt were painted in afterwards in 2d :)</P><P>Actually BUILDING your own 3d clothes needs a modelling rpgram and is tricky :/ I'd reocmmend Rhino3D to do that. <a href="http://www.rhino3d.com" target="_blank">www.rhino3d.com</a></P><P>Digital Blasphemy was hwat got me into 3d Art, saw pics there and just went WOW!!! :)</P><P>There's generally wyas around long render times, such as RENDER TO DISK usually is faster, and check each items' properties, reflection and volume = big render time, but you can often get around that by reducing reflection amounts, volume qualities etc to tweak render times :)</P><P>Redorious<BR>Archmage<BR>Karana</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/excalibur2thumb.jpg" border=0></a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
