        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Nice premise, story and art.</P><P>Not sure if you want any critques or not though.  More helpful suggestions really.  </P><P>Character weighting.  This is one of the TOUGHEST things for 3D artists to learn and do well.  It's easy to make a model and have it stand straight up, move the feet a little and be done.  Hard to make a warrior hiding behind a shield while wielding a sword and have them look like gravity is affecting them and they are bracing for an attack.  A lot of the time you really need to exaggerate the weighting to get across the right "feel".</P><P>Lighting seems a bit odd.  Looks like you have 3 maybe even 4 different lighting sources for the models and backgrounds.  Having everything lit from one direction does a lot to bringing the whole piece together instead of a collage.</P><P>Looks good in general though.</P><P><center><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank"><h4><font color=red>Kuotat Smith</h4></a>Baroness <s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr</font id=red><BR></center><BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
